{{Egypt-sports-venue-stub}}

{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{Use Australian English|date=January 2018}} In the sport of [[Australian rules football]], the '''half-back line''' refers to the positions of the 3 players on the field that occupy the centre half-back and left and right half-back flank positions.
{{Afl-field}}
==Centre half-back== The role of the centre half-back is similar to that of a defensive midfielder in association football. As the first line of defence, the centre half-back must aim to break down opposition attacks before they can get into a scoring position.<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28">Pascoe, 1995, p. 28</ref> Given that a centre half-back's opponent is usually the centre half-forward, the role is regarded as a ''key position'' in the team, and is usually reserved for tall and well-built players.
As one of the team's leaders, centre half-backs must be able to read the play and have good communication skills.<ref name=northey>{{cite web|url=http://www.swoopercoach.com.au/2010/playing-position-full-back/|title=Playing Position Centre Half Back|date=24 March 2010|first=John|last=Northey|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20121231005321/http://www.swoopercoach.com.au/2010/playing-position-full-back/|archivedate=31 December 2012|df=}}</ref> Although their first responsibility is to defend,<ref name=northey/> the great centre half-backs have proven to be equally creative in attack as well as reliable in defence.
Notable centre half-backs from over the years include: * [[Albert Chadwick]] ({{AFL Mel}} and {{AFL Haw}}, 1920–1929)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Walter Scott (Australian footballer)|Walter "Wacka" Scott]] ({{SANFL Nor}}, 1920–1932),<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.norwoodfc.com.au/HISTORY/TEAM_OF_THE_CENTURY.aspx|title=TEAM OF THE CENTURY|publisher=norwoodfc.com.au|accessdate=11 August 2012}}</ref> Magarey Medallist 1921, 1924, 1930 * [[Albert Collier|Albert "Leeter" Collier]] ({{AFL Col}} and {{AFL Fit}}, 1925–1941),<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29">Pascoe, 1995, p. 29</ref> Brownlow Medallist 1929 * [[Reg Hickey]] ({{AFL Gee}}, 1926–1940)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Denis Cordner]] (Melbourne, 1943–1956)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Ron Clegg]] ({{AFL SM}}, 1949–1960),<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> Brownlow medallist 1949 * [[Ian Shelton|Ian "Bluey" Shelton]] ({{AFL Ess}}, 1959–1965)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Peter Knights]] (Hawthorn, 1969–1985)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Bill Picken]] (Collingwood and {{AFL Syd}}, 1974–1986)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Jim Jess]] ({{AFL Ric}}, 1976–1988)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Ross Glendinning]] ({{AFL NM}} and {{AFL WC}}, 1978–1988),<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> Brownlow medallist 1983 * [[Paul Roos (Australian rules footballer)|Paul Roos]] (Fitzroy and Sydney, 1982–1998)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/> * [[Glen Jakovich]] (West Coast, 1991–2004)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 29"/>
==Half-back flank== The half-back flank was traditionally a defensive position, where reliability and toughness were more important than attacking flair.<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> In the modern game, reliability and toughness must now be combined with the ability to run and carry the ball as well as take on the opposition in a counter-attacking style.<ref name=coach>{{cite book|url=http://www.aflcommunityclub.com.au/fileadmin/user_upload/Coach_AFL/coaching_manual/2012_Youth_Coaching_Manual.pdf|title=AFL Youth Coaching Manual|page=92|chapter=Team Play and Game Plans: Position descriptions|year=2012|publisher=[[Australian Football League]]}}</ref>
Notable half-back flankers over the years in Australian football include: * [[Alec Epis]] ({{AFL Ess}}, 1958–1968)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Barry Davis (footballer)|Barry Davis]] (Essendon and {{AFL NM}}, 1961–1975)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[John Rantall]] ({{AFL SM}}, North Melbourne and {{AFL Fit}}, 1963–1980)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Ian Bremner]] ({{AFL Col}} and {{AFL Haw}}, 1966–1976)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Bruce Doull]] ({{AFL Car}}, 1969–1986),<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> Norm Smith Medallist 1981; Named Half-back flank in AFL Team of the Century (1996) * [[Stephen Wallis]] ({{AFL Foo}}, 1983–1996)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Ken Hinkley]] ({{AFL Fit}} and {{AFL Gee}}, 1987–1995)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Guy McKenna]] ({{AFL WC}}, 1988–2000)<ref name="Pascoe, 1995, p. 28"/> * [[Andrew McKay]] * [[Rohan Smith]] * [[Andrew McLeod]] * [[Nigel Smart]] * [[Luke Hodge]] * [[Brendon Goddard]] * [[Corey Enright]] * [[Shannon Hurn]] * [[Beau Waters]]
