{{Infobox company | name = International Shuffleboard Association (ISA) | type = 501(c)(3) non-profit organization | foundation = [[Saint Petersburg, Florida]] March 10, 1979 | key_people = President: Michael Zellner| industry = Shuffleboard | homepage = [http://www.world-shuffleboard.org www.world-shuffleboard.org] }}
The '''International Shuffleboard Association''' - ISA - was founded in [[Saint Petersburg, Florida]] in 1979.<ref>{{Cite web|title = SHUFFLEBOARD HISTORY – Page 2 of 2 {{!}} Court & Field Dimension Diagrams in 3D, History, Rules – SportsKnowHow.com|url = http://www.sportsknowhow.com/shuffleboard/history/shuffleboard-history-2.shtml|website = www.sportsknowhow.com|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref> [[Shuffleboard]] is a competitive game that is often played on ship decks or other large expanses of smooth outdoor surfaces and also at smaller scales on tables indoors. The ISA promotes Shuffleboard competition and travel worldwide. The 2009 Deck Shuffleboard championship in [[Zephyrhills, Florida]] at Betmar Shuffleboard Club featured 64 competitors.<ref>{{Cite web|title = World's top shuffleboard players to square off this week in Zephyrhills|url = http://www.tampabay.com/news/humaninterest/worlds-top-shuffleboard-players-to-square-off-this-week-in-zephyrhills/1043273|website = Tampa Bay Times|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title = INTERNATIONAL HOME PAGE|url = http://www.trigger.net/~sandy/isaboard.htm|website = www.trigger.net|accessdate = 2015-09-30}}</ref>
