{{Infobox football league | name = Kyushu Soccer League | logo = | pixels = | country = Japan | confed = [[Asian Football Confederation|AFC]] | founded = 1973 | folded = | divisions = 1 | teams = 11 | promotion = [[Japan Football League]] | relegation = Prefectural Leagues | levels = 5 | domest_cup = [[Emperor's Cup]] | confed_cup = | champions = [[J.FC MIYAZAKI]] | season = 2016 | most successful club = Kitakyushu FC (8) | website = http://www.kyu-league.jp/ | current = [[2017 Japanese Regional Leagues]] }}
The {{nihongo|'''Kyushu Soccer League'''|九州サッカーリーグ|}} is a Japanese amateur football league, covering the prefecture of eight prefectures ([[Fukuoka Prefecture|Fukuoka]], [[Saga Prefecture|Saga]], [[Nagasaki Prefecture|Nagasaki]], [[Kumamoto Prefecture|Kumamoto]], [[Ōita Prefecture|Oita]], [[Miyazaki Prefecture|Miyazaki]], [[Kagoshima Prefecture|Kagoshima]] and [[Okinawa Prefecture|Okinawa]]).
