{{Infobox GAA player | code= Hurling | sport = Hurling | image = | name = Liam Keoghan | irish = Liam Mac Eochagáin | | fullname =Liam Keoghan | | height = | nickname = | county = Kilkenny | province = Leinster | club = [[Tullaroan GAA|Tullaroan]] | clposition = Right half-back | clubs = | clyears = 1980s-2000s | clapps(points) = | clcounty = 1 | clprovince= 0 | clallireland = 0 | counties = [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] | icposition = Right wing-back | icyears = 1993-1998 | icapps(points) = | icprovince = 2 | icallireland = 1 | allstars = 1 | nhl = 1 | clupdate= | icupdate= | birth_place=[[Tullaroan]], [[County Kilkenny]] }} '''Liam Keoghan''' (born 1968 in [[Tullaroan]], [[County Kilkenny]]) is an [[Irish people|Irish]] retired sportsperson. He played [[hurling]] with his local club [[Tullaroan GAA|Tullaroan]] and was a member of the [[Kilkenny GAA|Kilkenny]] senior inter-county team from 1993 until 1998. Keoghan won an All-Ireland senior medal with the Cats in 1993, and in 1997 became the first player in Tullaroan history to capture an All-Star Award.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record%3D4 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2011-09-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928025201/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=4 |archivedate=2011-09-28 |df= }}</ref>
Keoghan was rewarded for his successes on the field with a place on the Tullaroan Team of the Century.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=4 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-05-12 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110928025201/http://www.kilkennycats.com/clubs/cgi-bin/cginews.pl?record=4 |archivedate=2011-09-28 |df= }}</ref>
