{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=May 2018}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Northern Railway Stadium | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Northern Railway Stadium | former names = | location = [[Bikaner]], [[Rajasthan]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 1976 | built = | opened = 1976 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Northern Railway zone|Northern Railway]] | operator = [[Northern Railway zone|Northern Railway]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/india/content/ground/57968.html Cricinfo] | publictransit = }} '''Northern Railway Stadium''' is a multi purpose stadium in [[Bikaner]], [[Rajasthan]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports. The stadium has hosted five [[First-class cricket|first-class]] matches <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/943_f.html First-class matches]</ref> in 1976 when [[Rajasthan cricket team]] played against [[Vidarbha cricket team]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/36/36665.html Scorecard]</ref> The ground hosted four more [[First-class cricket|first-class]] matches from 1978 to 1995. The stadium also hosted two [[List A]] matches when [[Willis XI]] played against [[Madhya Pradesh cricket team]] <ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/32/32162.html Scorecard] </ref> and against [[Central Zone cricket team]] played against [[West Zone cricket team]]<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/943_a.html List A matches]</ref> but since then the stadium has hosted non-first-class matches.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/943_misc.html Other matches]</ref>
