{{Infobox sports team | name = Rugby Nova Scotia | Photo = | logo = Rugbyu12.jpg | full_name = Nova Scotia Rugby Union (NSRU) | association = [[Rugby Canada|Rugby Canda]] | location = Nova Scotia, Canada | colours =
}}
'''Rugby Nova Scotia''' is the provincial administrative body for [[rugby union]] in [[Nova Scotia]], Canada.
==Summary== [[File:Mini-Rugby.jpg|thumb|left|Youth playing Flag Rugby at the Conrose Park in Halifax]] The '''Nova Scotia Rugby Union''' (ORU) also known as '''[http://rugbyns.ns.ca Rugby Nova Scotia]'''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rugbyns.ns.ca|title=Rugby Nova Scotia Homepage|last=Nova Scotia|first=Rugby|website=http://rugbyns.ns.ca|access-date=2016-09-15}}</ref> is the provincial governing body for the sport of [[rugby union]] in the [[Canada|Canadian]] province of [[Nova Scotia]] and a Provincial Union of [[Rugby Canada]]. Rugby Nova Scotia governs various levels of rugby (Mini-Rugby, Under-12, Under-14, Under-16, Under-18, Senior, Masters, Non-contact).
You can find a list of clubs in Nova Scotia [http://rugbyns.ns.ca/content_page/10022420/ here].
==High Performance Program== Rugby Nova Scotia is represented on the National stage by the [[Nova Scotia Keltics]]. This program includes 15's teams at the following ages: U15, U16, U17, U18, U19, U20 and Senior; which compete at the Canadian Rugby Championship in championship and festival divisions. In 2009, [[Rugby Canada]] decided to disband the RCSL and replace it with a new U-20 league called the [[Rugby Canada National Junior Championship]]. The Keltics were chosen as one of the remaining RCSL clubs to enter the newly formed league.
