{{Infobox venue | stadium_name = Nabeul Indoor Complex | nickname = | image = | fullname = Nabeul Bir Challouf Indoor Complex | former names = | location = [[Nabeul]], [[Tunisia]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2004 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor= | project_manager = | main_contractors = | former_names = | tenants = [[Stade Nabeulien]] | seating_capacity = 5,000 | }}
The '''Nabeul Bir Challouf Indoor Sports Complex''' is an [[indoor arena|indoor sporting arena]] located in [[Nabeul]], [[Tunisia]], and it is the home of the [[Tunisia|Tunisian]] [[Basketball]] Club [[Stade Nabeulien]] The capacity of the arena is 5,000 spectators.<ref>[https://foursquare.com/v/salle-couverte-des-sports-collectifs/543d4217498e3726db835d49?openPhotoId=5797a875498e840eeade9ef6 Some photos] {{fr icon}}</ref>.
==Events== The Nabeul Sports Complex was built specifically to host some of the [[2005 FIBA Under-19 World Championship for Women]] matches and has also hosted many [[2005 World Men's Handball Championship]] matches later and since it became home of the Stade Nabeulien Basketball team.
The Sports Indoor Complex is used for many sports disciplines like [[volleyball]], [[basketball]], [[handball]], [[wrestling]], [[karate]], [[judo]], [[taekwondo]] and also the arena hosts many politics events and concerts.
