{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Stade Alfred Marie-Jeanne | image = | location = [[Rivière-Pilote]], [[Martinique]], [[France]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = | opened = 1991 | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Rivière-Pilote|Commune of Rivière-Pilote]] | operator = | surface = | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = Stade (municipal) En Camée | tenants = [[RC Rivière-Pilote|Racing Club de Rivière-Pilote]] | seating_capacity = 3,000 }}
The '''Stade Alfred Marie-Jeanne''', until August 2011 ''Stade En Camée'', is a [[multi-purpose stadium]] located in [[Rivière-Pilote]], [[Martinique]], an [[overseas department]] of [[France]].<ref>http://freesporting.com/area.ist.html?lang=ka&area=34437 Stade En Camée</ref> It is currently used mostly for [[Association football|football]] matches and is set to be utilized as a venue for the [[2010 Caribbean Championship]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dcc.digicelfootball.com/news/62-digicel-cup-qualifiers-set-up-dramatic-finals |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-11-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110710125748/http://dcc.digicelfootball.com/news/62-digicel-cup-qualifiers-set-up-dramatic-finals |archivedate=2011-07-10 |df= }} Digicel Cup Set Up Dramatic Finals</ref>
